      <title>2012 election prediction maps</title>
      <link>http://vielmetti.github.io/post/2012/2012-11-03-2012-election-prediction-maps/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 03 Nov 2012 14:42:11 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://vielmetti.github.io/post/2012/2012-11-03-2012-election-prediction-maps/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;From Nate Silver&amp;#39;s NY Times weblog &lt;a href=&#34;http://fivethirtyeight.blogs.nytimes.com/&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;FiveThirtyEight&lt;/a&gt;, captured Saturday, November 3, 2012:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d3fbaa3970c-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Picture 62&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d3fbaa3970c&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d3fbaa3970c-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Picture 62&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;http://graphics.latimes.com/2012-election-electoral-map/&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;Los Angeles Times electoral map&lt;/a&gt;, again a prediction from Saturday. Note that this analysis doesn&amp;#39;t give exact numerical predictions. The Chicago Tribune links to the same map.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d3fc026970c-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Picture 63&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d3fc026970c&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d3fc026970c-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Picture 63&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;#0160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Detroit Free Press runs with&amp;#0160;&lt;a href=&#34;http://realclearpolitics.com/epolls/2012/president/2012_elections_electoral_college_map.html&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;a map from Real Clear Politics&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b56c66970d-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Picture 64&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b56c66970d&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b56c66970d-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Picture 64&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-09-21/2012-us-presidential-election-map-interactive/4272242&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;Australian Broadcasting Company (ABC) interactive map&lt;/a&gt;, showing toss-up states in orange:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017c3311564c970b-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Picture 65&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017c3311564c970b&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017c3311564c970b-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Picture 65&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks to Naomi Zikmund-Fisher, here are a few more:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From &lt;a href=&#34;http://electoral-vote.com/&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;Electoral-Vote.com&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b5d1b6970d-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Picture 66&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b5d1b6970d&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b5d1b6970d-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Picture 66&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;From &lt;a href=&#34;http://election.princeton.edu/&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;election.princeton.edu&lt;/a&gt;, this map that shows equal area based on electoral votes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b5d583970d-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Picture 67&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b5d583970d&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b5d583970d-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Picture 67&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A second distorted map, this one from &lt;a href=&#34;http://frontloading.blogspot.com/&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;Frontloading HQ&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d41e3c2970c-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Electoral.college.map.2012_10.31&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d41e3c2970c&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d41e3c2970c-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Electoral.college.map.2012_10.31&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.electionprojection.com/2012elections/president12.php&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;ElectionProjection.com&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b5d92f970d-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Picture 68&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b5d92f970d&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017ee4b5d92f970d-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Picture 68&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Finally, this NPR map shows campaign spending by state, with the size of the state adjusted to match where the money is going. From the story &amp;quot;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.npr.org/blogs/itsallpolitics/2012/11/01/163632378/a-campaign-map-morphed-by-money&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;A campaign map morphed by money&lt;/a&gt;&amp;quot;, this clearly shows which states are battleground states:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d405266970c-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Bbstates_custom-e0c6c871e5a185100d0be94271fba73c0a365998-s4&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d405266970c&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef017d3d405266970c-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Bbstates_custom-e0c6c871e5a185100d0be94271fba73c0a365998-s4&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Look for more maps here on election night - if you find any more or know of any other that are good leave a comment and I&amp;#39;ll add them in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;#0160;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
